            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Hd1e108">Rubrica 10</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De confidentia: credulitate et credulis atque incredulis</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>
      ¶ De confidentia credulitate cre
      <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>dulis atque incredulis. Rubrica. 10
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e121">
               <lb ed="#V" n="77"/>Socrates in exorta
      <lb ed="#V" n="78" break="no"/>tionibus:
      <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>c. 2. <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e129">Expedire putes non esse credem
        <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>dum temerariis prout credendum probis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e135">
               <lb ed="#V" n="81"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e139">¶ Aristoteles rethoricorum. lib. i. c. 2. Mode
        <lb ed="#V" n="82" break="no"/>stis credimus magis et scelerius </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e146"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e148"> Lib. et. c.
        <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>16. Iuuenes sunt faciles creditiui: propterea
        <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>quod nondum in multis decepti sunt. Iuuenes
        <lb ed="#V" n="85"/>facile seducibiles sunt: sperant enim facile. Se
        <lb ed="#V" n="86"/>nes increduli sunt: propter experientiam. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e160">
               <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e164">¶ Iesus filius sirach in eccl. c. 12. Non cre
        <lb ed="#V" n="88" break="no"/>das inimico tuo in eternum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e170"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e172"> c. 19. Qui cre
        <lb ed="#V" n="89" break="no"/>dit cito leuis est corde: et minorabitur.
        <lb ed="#V" n="90"/>Non omni verbo credas. <!--96.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="35-r"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
               </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e186">
               <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e190">¶ Tullius retho. artis vereris li. i. c. 12. Sun
        <lb ed="#V" n="2" break="no"/>ma amentia est in eorum fide spem habere quo
        <lb ed="#V" n="3" break="no"/>rum perfidia deceptus sis multotiens. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e198"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e200"> Lib. et
        <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>c. 9. Fidentia est per quam magnis et hone
        <lb ed="#V" n="5" break="no"/>stis rebus: multum ipse animus in se fiducia
        <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>certa cum spe collocauit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e210">
               <lb ed="#V" n="7"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e214">¶ Quidius epistolarum. epi 1n6. Credulitas
        <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>danno solet esse puellis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e221"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e223"> Idem de arte aman
        <lb ed="#V" n="9"/>di li. 3. et fi. Nec ciro credideris: quantum cito
        <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>credere ledat. Exemplum nobis no leue pro
        <lb ed="#V" n="11" break="no"/>crus erit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e233"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e235"> Idem de tristibus li. 4. e. 3
        <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>Crede quod est et vis: ac desine tuta vereri.
        <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>Deque fide certa: sit tibi certa fides. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e243">
               <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e247">/ Seneca declam. li. 5. c. i. Nemo facile cre
        <lb ed="#V" n="15" break="no"/>dit: quo credito sit dolendum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e253"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e255"> Idem in pro
        <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>uerb. Utrumque vitium est: et omnibus credere et nulli. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e261">
               <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e265">¶ Ioannes apostolus et euange. in epistola vnica. c. 4.
        <lb ed="#V" n="18"/>Nolite credere omni spiritui: sed probate spiri
        <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>tus si ex deo sunt. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e273">
               <lb ed="#V" n="20"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e277">¶ Marcialis cocus li. vndique. suscepto. c. 5.
        <lb ed="#V" n="21"/>Omnibus et nulli te credere vitium est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e284">
               <lb ed="#V" n="22"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e288">¶ Uegetius de re mili. li. 3. ti. 3 Frequentius
        <lb ed="#V" n="23"/>conuentionum pacisque simulatio credulis no
        <lb ed="#V" n="24"/>cuere quam arma. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e296">
               <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e300">¶ Auctor lib. de for. honeste vite. ca. 4. Ru
        <lb ed="#V" n="26" break="no"/>moribus criminum et suspitionibus minime
        <lb ed="#V" n="27"/>sis credulus: sed potius malignis qui per spe
        <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>ciem simplicitatis ad nocendum aliquibus sub
        <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>repunt oppositi simus. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e312">
               <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e316">¶ Ambrosius de officiis li. i. c. 31. Unusquis
        <lb ed="#V" n="31" break="no"/>que bene volentis se magis quam sapientis credit
        <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>consilio </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e324"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e326"> Libro. 2t. c. 8. Promptius nos iu
        <lb ed="#V" n="33" break="no"/>sto viro quam prudenti committimus. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e332">
               <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e336">¶ Fulgentius li. 3. et fi. fabula. 15. Creduli
        <lb ed="#V" n="35" break="no"/>tas semper deceptionum mater est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e342">
               <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e346">¶ Cato. c. i. Nil temere credideris. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e351"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e353"> Ca. 3
        <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>Noli tum quedam referenti credere semper.
        <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>Exigua est tribuenda fides: quia multi mul
        <lb ed="#V" n="39"/>ta loquuntur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e363">
               <lb ed="#V" n="40"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e367">¶ Cassiodorus epistolarum li. 3. e. 4. Illi credere
        <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>debetis quem vestris vtilitatibus arridem co
        <lb ed="#V" n="42" break="no"/>gnoscitis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e375">
               <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e379">¶ Uersificator fabularum esopi. fab. 9. Non
        <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>satis est tutum mellitis credere verbis.
        <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>Ex hoc melle: solet pestis amara sequi. <!--96.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
               </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e391">
               <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e395">¶ Fabula. 25. Tpre non omni: non omnibus omnia cre
        <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>das. Qui misere credit: creditur esse miser. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e401">
               <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e405">¶ Fabula 31. Qui me lesit: idem ledet si lede
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>re posset. Expedit insido: non interare fidem.
        <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>Que dedit infidus mella venena puto. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e413">
               <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e417">¶ Ualdo fabula. 11. Nec confidatis secreta
        <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>nec his detegatis. Cum quibus egistis: pu
        <lb ed="#V" n="53" break="no"/>gne discrimina tristis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e426"> ¶
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e428">/ Fabula. 26
        <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>Nulla fidis hosti tibi sit.
        <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>Prorsus et hostilis: tibi sit suasio vilis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e436">
               <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e440">¶ Mattheus vindocinensis in poetria: parte
        <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>i. c. 20. Credulitas sestina nocet. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e446">
               <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e450">¶ Prouerb. vulgar: Et passiu non cre al zuno
        <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>Tuto crere noe sauere. </quote>
            </p>
         </div>
